    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the author's intent in his original context and the psalm's canonical trajectory. The movements below trace Psalm 21's argument from its retrospective praise through its theological pivot and divine-warrior confidence to its doxological close. The psalm requires reading at two levels: the historical David and his court, and the messianic king to whom the psalm's language finally points.",
